{"type":"message","id":"3218a44b","parentId":"69d55838","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:28:12.811Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-03-24 00:28 EDT] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: SSH to Modal or run a simple test: modal run a quick function that checks if /usr/local/bin/ollama exists and can show its version. Then try to start it and see if it works. File: C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py. Just check if ollama binary is there and its version."}],"timestamp":1774326492809}}
{"type":"message","id":"95054362","parentId":"3218a44b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:28:18.860Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the modal_spark.py file to understand its structure, then check if I can run a modal command to check for ollama.","thinkingSignature":"4682177e4165965e1425aed27c9173ece53060c052221cbd89567c993f394722"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hqp76wqv4v9v_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\modal_spark.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":19,"output":73,"cacheRead":1307,"cacheWrite":8787,"totalTokens":10186,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326492810}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca1e694d","parentId":"95054362","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:28:18.947Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hqp76wqv4v9v_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama — FastAPI + Ollama + Eval Harness on Modal A100.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nimport statistics\nimport os\nimport asyncio\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\nOLLAMA_PORT = 11434\nMODEL_NAME = \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n\n# ─── Benchmark prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nGSM8K = [\n    \"There are 15 trees in the grove. Grove workers will plant trees in the orchard today. When they finished, there were 21 trees in the orchard. How many trees did they plant today?\",\n    \"Leah has 6 apples and 4 oranges, and she eats 2 fruits. How many fruits does she have left?\",\n    \"A clown has 12 balloons. He gives away 5 to children. Later he buys 8 more balloons. How many balloons does he have now?\",\n    \"Tom has 5 baseball cards. He buys 3 more packs with 4 cards each. How many cards does he have total?\",\n    \"There are 3 pink flowers and 4 blue flowers in a vase. Sarah puts 2 more pink flowers in the vase. How many flowers are in the vase?\",\n]\n\nREASONING = [\n    \"If all Zeps are Mors, and some Mors are Leps, could some Zeps be Leps? Explain your reasoning.\",\n    \"Complete the pattern: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?\",\n    \"What is heavier: a pound of feathers or a pound of bricks?\",\n    \"If it takes 5 machines 5 minutes to make 5 widgets, how long would it take 100 machines to make 100 widgets?\",\n    \"A farmer has 17 sheep. All but 9 die. How many are left?\",\n]\n\nCODE = [\n    \"Write a Python function to check if a string is a palindrome.\",\n    \"Write a Python function that returns the nth Fibonacci number using iteration.\",\n    \"Write a Python function to find the maximum element in a list without using max().\",\n]\n\n# ─── Image ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx>=0.28.0\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd\",\n        \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n)\n\n# ─── UI HTML ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nUI_HTML = \"\"\"<!DOCTYPE html><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\"/><title>SPARK Eval</title><style>\n*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;background:#0f0f13;color:#e0e0e0;min-height:100vh}\n#root{padding:2rem;max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto}h1{color:#fff;margin-bottom:1.5rem}\n.card{background:#1a1a22;border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border:1px solid #2a2a35}\n.card h2{color:#a0a0b0;font-size:.8rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em;margin-bottom:1rem}\nbutton{background:#6366f1;color:white;border:none;padding:.6rem 1.2rem;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;font-size:.9rem;font-weight:500}\nbutton:hover{background:#4f46e5}button:disabled{background:#3a3a4a;cursor:not-allowed}\n.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:.75rem}\n.stat-card{background:#14141c;border-radius:8px;padding:.9rem;border:1px solid #252530}\n.stat-card h3{color:#fff;margin-bottom:.4rem;font-size:.95rem}\n.s{color:#707080;font-size:.82rem;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:.2rem 0}\n.s span{color:#c0c0d0;font-family:monospace}\n.res{margin-top:.8rem;padding-top:.8rem;border-top:1px solid #252530}\n.q{color:#888898;font-size:.82rem;margin-bottom:.4rem}\n.a{color:#d0d0e0;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.5;background:#101018;padding:.7rem;border-radius:6px;white-space:pre-wrap}\n.lat{color:#6366f1;font-size:.75rem;margin-top:.3rem}\n.expander{cursor:pointer;padding:.4rem 0}.expander:hover{color:#fff}\n.header{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;margin-bottom:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.8rem}\n.badge{background:#252530;padding:.35rem .75rem;border-radius:6px;font-size:.78rem;color:#a0a0b0}\ninput{background:#14141c;border:1px solid #252530;color:#e0e0e0;padding:.6rem;border-radius:8px;font-size:.9rem;flex:1}\n.gen-form{display:flex;gap:.5rem;margin-bottom:.8rem}\n.status{font-size:.8rem}.ok{color:#22c55e}.err{color:#ef4444}.warn{color:#f59e0b}\n</style></head><body><div id=\"root\"></div>\n<script type=\"module\">\nimport React,{useState,useEffect}from\"react\";import ReactDOM from\"react-dom/client\";import axios from\"axios\"\nconst API=\"\"\nconst App=()=>{\n  const[benchmarks,setBenchmarks]=useState(null)\n  const[loading,setLoading]=useState(false)\n  const[health,setHealth]=useState(null)\n  const[expanded,setExpanded]=useState({})\n  const[prompt,setPrompt]=useState(\"\")\n  const[genResult,setGenResult]=useState(null)\n  const[genning,setGening]=useState(false)\n  useEffect(()=>{(async()=>{try{const r=await axios.get(API+\"/health\");setHealth(r.data)}catch(e){setHealth({status:\"error\",error:e.message})}})()},[])\n  const run=async()=>{setLoading(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/benchmarks\");setBenchmarks(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setLoading(false)}\n  const send=async(e)=>{e.preventDefault();if(!prompt.trim())return;setGening(true);try{const r=await axios.post(API+\"/generate\",{prompt,temperature:.7,num_predict:300});setGenResult(r.data)}catch(e){alert(e.message)};setGening(false)}\n  const toggle=(b,i)=>{const k=b+\"-\"+i;setExpanded(p=>({...p,[k]:!p[k]}))}\n  const healthColor=health?.ollama===\"ready\"?\"ok\":health?.ollama===\"starting\"?\"warn\":\"err\"\n  const healthText=health?.ollama===\"ready\"?\"Ollama Ready\":health?.ollama===\"starting\"?\"Starting Ollama...\":\"Ollama Offline\"\n  return React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"header\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h1\",null,\"SPARK Eval\"),\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{style:{display:\"flex\",gap:\"1rem\",alignItems:\"center\"}},\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"badge\"},\"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n        React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"status \"+healthColor},healthText),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{onClick:run,disabled:loading},loading?\"Running...\":\"Run Benchmarks\")\n      )\n    ),\n    React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Chat\"),\n      React.createElement(\"form\",{className:\"gen-form\",onSubmit:send},\n        React.createElement(\"input\",{value:prompt,onChange:e=>setPrompt(e.target.value),placeholder:\"Ask the model...\"}),\n        React.createElement(\"button\",{type:\"submit\",disabled:genning},genning?\"...\":\"Send\")\n      ),\n      genResult&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},genResult.response)\n    ),\n    benchmarks&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n      React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Results\"),\n        React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"grid\"},\n          benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"stat-card\"},\n            React.createElement(\"h3\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Prompts\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.num_prompts)),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Avg Latency\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.avg_latency_s+\"s\")),\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"s\"},React.createElement(\"span\",null,\"Total Time\"),React.createElement(\"span\",null,b.total_time_s+\"s\"))\n          ))\n        )\n      ),\n      benchmarks.benchmarks.map(b=>React.createElement(\"div\",{key:b.name,className:\"card\"},\n        React.createElement(\"h2\",null,b.name.toUpperCase()+\" Responses\"),\n        b.results.map((r,i)=>{\n          const k=b.name+\"-\"+i\n          return React.createElement(\"div\",{key:i,className:\"res\"},\n            React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"expander\",onClick:()=>toggle(b.name,i)},\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{className:\"q\"},\"Q: \"+r.prompt.slice(0,85)+(r.prompt.length>85?\"...\":\"\")),\n              React.createElement(\"span\",{style:{color:\"#6366f1\",fontSize:\".75rem\",marginLeft:\".5rem\"}},expanded[k]?\"▲\":\"▼\")\n            ),\n            expanded[k]&&React.createElement(\"div\",null,\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"a\"},\"A: \"+r.response),\n              React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"lat\"},r.latency_s+\"s\")\n            )\n          )\n        })\n      ))\n    ),\n    !benchmarks&&!loading&&React.createElement(\"div\",{className:\"card\"},\n      React.createElement(\"h2\",null,\"Ready\"),\n      React.createElement(\"p\",{style:{color:\"#707080\",fontSize:\".88rem\"}},'Click \"Run Benchmarks\" to evaluate the model.')\n    )\n  )\n}\nReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById(\"root\")).render(React.createElement(App))\n</script></body></html>\"\"\"\n\n\n# ─── Shared ollama state (module level so it persists across requests) ─────────\n\n_ollama_state = {\n    \"status\": \"unknown\",  # unknown | starting | ready | error\n    \"proc\": None,\n}\n\n\ndef _start_ollama_bg():\n    \"\"\"Non-blocking Ollama start — runs in background thread, updates shared state.\"\"\"\n    import httpx\n    import subprocess\n\n    if _ollama_state[\"status\"] in (\"starting\", \"ready\"):\n        return\n\n    _ollama_state[\"status\"] = \"starting\"\n\n    try:\n        # Start Ollama server\n        proc = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"serve\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", str(OLLAMA_PORT)],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n        )\n        _ollama_state[\"proc\"] = proc\n\n        # Wait for API\n        for i in range(30):\n            try:\n                with httpx.Client(timeout=5) as c:\n                    r = c.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/\")\n                    if r.status_code == 200:\n                        break\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n            import time; time.sleep(2)\n        else:\n            _ollama_state[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n            return\n\n        # Check if model present\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"list\"], capture_output=True, text=True,\n        )\n        if MODEL_NAME not in result.stdout:\n            # Pull model (this takes a while)\n            pull = subprocess.Popen(\n                [\"/usr/local/bin/ollama\", \"pull\", MODEL_NAME],\n                stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            )\n            pull.wait()\n            if pull.returncode != 0:\n                _ollama_state[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n                return\n\n        _ollama_state[\"status\"] = \"ready\"\n        print(\"Ollama ready with model\", MODEL_NAME)\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        _ollama_state[\"status\"] = \"error\"\n        print(\"Ollama start error:\", e)\n\n\n@app.function(image=_image, timeout=3600, scaledown_window=600)\n@modal.asgi_app(label=\"spark-ollama\")\ndef api():\n    from fastapi import FastAPI\n    from fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse\n    import httpx\n\n    api = FastAPI()\n\n    @api.get(\"/\", response_class=HTMLResponse)\n    async def root():\n        return HTMLResponse(content=UI_HTML, status_code=200)\n\n    @api.get(\"/health\")\n    async def health():\n        # Trigger background start if not started\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] == \"unknown\":\n            # Fire and forget — start in background thread\n            loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()\n            loop.run_in_executor(None, _start_ollama_bg)\n\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"ok\",\n            \"ollama\": _ollama_state[\"status\"],\n            \"model\": MODEL_NAME,\n        }\n\n    @api.post(\"/generate\")\n    async def generate(req: dict):\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] != \"ready\":\n            return {\"error\": f\"Ollama not ready (status: {_ollama_state['status']})\"}\n\n        prompt = req.get(\"prompt\", \"\")\n        temperature = req.get(\"temperature\", 0.7)\n        num_predict = req.get(\"num_predict\", 300)\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n            r = await c.post(\n                f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                      \"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": num_predict, \"stream\": False}\n            )\n            r.raise_for_status()\n            return r.json()\n\n    @api.post(\"/benchmarks\")\n    async def benchmarks():\n        if _ollama_state[\"status\"] != \"ready\":\n            return {\"error\": f\"Ollama not ready (status: {_ollama_state['status']}). Try again in a few minutes.\"}\n\n        BENCHMARK_PROMPTS = {\"gsm8k\": GSM8K, \"reasoning\": REASONING, \"code\": CODE}\n        results = {\"benchmarks\": [], \"timestamp\": time.time()}\n        for bench_name, prompts in BENCHMARK_PROMPTS.items():\n            bench_results, latencies = [], []\n            for prompt in prompts:\n                t0 = time.perf_counter()\n                try:\n                    async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120.0) as c:\n                        r = await c.post(\n                            f\"http://127.0.0.1:{OLLAMA_PORT}/api/generate\",\n                            json={\"model\": MODEL_NAME, \"prompt\": prompt,\n                                  \"temperature\": 0.7, \"num_predict\": 300, \"stream\": False}\n                        )\n                        r.raise_for_status()\n                        response_text = r.json().get(\"response\", \"\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    response_text = f\"ERROR: {str(e)}\"\n                latency = time.perf_counter() - t0\n                latencies.append(latency)\n                bench_results.append({\"prompt\": prompt, \"response\": response_text, \"latency_s\": round(latency, 3)})\n            results[\"benchmarks\"].append({\n                \"name\": bench_name, \"num_prompts\": len(prompts),\n                \"avg_latency_s\": round(statistics.mean(latencies), 3),\n                \"total_time_s\": round(sum(latencies), 3), \"results\": bench_results,\n            })\n        return results\n\n    return api\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef main():\n    print(\"Deploying SPARK to Modal...\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326498907}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0ad4547","parentId":"ca1e694d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:28:29.065Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the modal_spark.py file. The task is to SSH to Modal or run a quick test to check if `/usr/local/bin/ollama` exists and can show its version.\n\nThe way to run Modal is via the `modal` CLI. Let me try running a quick modal command to check for ollama. I can use `modal run` with a simple script, or I could try to shell into the container.\n\nActually, looking at the task more carefully: \"SSH to Modal or run a simple test: modal run a quick function that checks if /usr/local/bin/ollama exists and can show its version.\"\n\n\nI'll create a simple Modal function that checks if the ollama binary exists and retrieves its version, then execute it through the modal CLI.","thinkingSignature":"594ce4b537748fd37e356f4ca6112fa04a00d154abbb1771fb7febaf9f1a751b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_troxjc5xtsx3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark && modal run --help 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3926,"output":212,"cacheRead":9958,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14096,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326498948}}
