{"type":"message","id":"ee3ffe20","parentId":"365adba9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:28:44.109Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me create a simple test script to check for ollama on Modal. I'll create a temporary script that just checks for the binary and its version.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the `modal run` command runs a function defined in a Python file. I need to create a simple function that can be deployed to Modal and check for ollama.\n\nThe simplest approach is to create a quick one-off script that uses Modal's image with the ollama binary already present (since the main app installs it via the install script).\n\nActually wait - the task says to SSH to Modal OR run a quick test. Let me think about what's available. \n\nI need to write a test function that runs on Modal's infrastructure and checks for the ollama binary. The function should execute on the container where ollama was installed via the install script, so it'll be available at `/usr/local/bin/ollama`. I'll create a temporary script and run it with `modal run`.","thinkingSignature":"f2cdcd7403eb0b2aaf8ee160620d52015f369e539b9692096378826fa9b5f6f3"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me create a quick test script to check for ollama on the Modal sandbox:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_knd1wdywpg7l_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\spark\\test_ollama.py","content":"\"\"\"Quick test: check if ollama binary exists and show version.\"\"\"\nimport subprocess\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"test-ollama\")\n\n_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"fastapi\", \"uvicorn[standard]\", \"httpx>=0.28.0\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd\",\n        \"curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n)\n\n@app.function(image=_image, timeout=120)\ndef check_ollama():\n    import subprocess\n\n    ollama_path = \"/usr/local/bin/ollama\"\n    result = subprocess.run([\"test\", \"-f\", ollama_path], capture_output=True)\n    if result.returncode != 0:\n        print(f\"FAIL: {ollama_path} does not exist\")\n        return {\"exists\": False, \"path\": ollama_path}\n\n    print(f\"OK: {ollama_path} exists\")\n\n    version_result = subprocess.run(\n        [ollama_path, \"--version\"], capture_output=True, text=True\n    )\n    version = version_result.stdout.strip() or version_result.stderr.strip() or \"unknown\"\n    print(f\"Version output: {version}\")\n\n    # Also try ollama list\n    list_result = subprocess.run(\n        [ollama_path, \"list\"], capture_output=True, text=True\n    )\n    print(f\"ollama list:\\n{list_result.stdout}\")\n    if list_result.stderr:\n        print(f\"ollama list stderr:\\n{list_result.stderr}\")\n\n    return {\n        \"exists\": True,\n        \"path\": ollama_path,\n        \"version\": version,\n        \"list_stdout\": list_result.stdout,\n        \"list_stderr\": list_result.stderr,\n    }\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef main():\n    result = check_ollama.remote()\n    print(\"Result:\", result)\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4194,"output":681,"cacheRead":9958,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14833,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326510851}}
